data.text:
Synopsis

American actress, Demi Moore is having a revival. The actress is famous for her characters in films such as "Ghost", "A Few Good Men", "Indecent Proposal". In the show, Demi Moore plays the role of Ann Woodward, the former New York socialite, who dropped from grace in the 1950s mid at the time of accusations leveled against her for killing her husband.

Demi Moore, an American actress is having a renewal. The actress is renowned for her characters in several of the most famous films from the 1980s and 1990's which include "A Few Good Men", "Indecent Proposal", "And ghost". Though she has made an appearance in some projects in the recent times, the roles she has acted in have been somewhat limited.

Where is Demi Moore presently acting in?

Demi Moore has reached a new summit in Hollywood as she is presently being starred in the thoroughly expected second season of the anthology series of Ryan Murphy "Feud" and will be appearing in a series which is created by Taylor Sheridan.

Only two months of the new year, the first big project by Demi Moore in a span of years "Feud: Capote vs The Swans" has made its debut on FX. The show follows the famous conflict of Truman Capote with the most renowned socialites, called the Swans.

What role is Demi Moore playing in the show?

In the show, Demi Moore plays the role of Ann Woodward, the former New York socialite, who is dropping from grace in the 1950s mid at the time of accusations leveled against her for killing her husband. While Woodward did kill her husband, no crime allegations were charged against her with police believing her story that she thought he was a trespasser.

Her conquest in high society was further enhanced by her former friend, Capote, having gossips about her all through the town, imbuing doubt in her story and stating that she wanted to murder her husband. She had died by suicide in the year 1975 after the rumors about her in an Esquire article.

Demi Moore told "Good Morning America" in January, 2024 that according to her, one feels great responsibility when they are deciding to be playing a real person.
